<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>
    Muffinland page <%= muffin_number %>:
  </title>
</head>
<body>

<p>----- start of page <%= muffin_number %> -----</p>

<%= muffin_contents %>

<p>----- end of page <%= muffin_number %> -----</p>


<form method="post" action="">
  <p>Go ahead and add page <%= next_available_muffin_number %>:
    <input type="text" name="MuffinContents" value="" >
    <input type="submit" name="AddNewMuffin" value="Add New Muffin"></p>
  <p>Tag it as belonging to a page? page:
    <input type="text" name="CollectionNumber" value="" >
    <input type="submit" name="PutMuffinIntoCollection" value="Put Muffin Into Collection"></p>
</form>


<p> Otherwise, choose from one of these pages:</p>

<ul>
  <% @myPosts.each_with_index {|muffin, index|
    who = muffin.ip
    who = "Poor Alistair locked in his dungeon" if muffin.ip == "86.193.109.86"
    who = "Poor Alistair locked in his dungeon" if muffin.ip == "::1"
  %>

      <li> <a href=<%=index%> > page <%=index%> </a>, submitted from <%= who %>
      </li>
  <% }  %>
</ul>


<hr />

<pre>
<p> Tech notes:</p>
<p> Path sent in was "<%= path %>" </p>
<p> Params were <%= params %></p>
</pre>

<p> You did good. <br />
  Yes, I know that's bad English.
</p>
<img src="http://alistair.cockburn.us/get/1830">






</body>
</html>

